/*==============================================================================
USER-SPECIFIC CONFIGURATION TEMPLATE
================================================================================

Instructions:
1. Copy this file to config.do:
   - Windows: copy config.do.template config.do
   - macOS/Linux: cp config.do.template config.do

2. Edit config.do to set your local data path

3. config.do is gitignored - never commit it to version control

Note: If config.do doesn't exist, the template defaults to data/ in project root

==============================================================================*/

/*------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    DATA PATH CONFIGURATION
------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

// OPTION 1: Data stored separately from code (RECOMMENDED for shared drives)
// Uncomment and edit the path below:

// global data_root "X:/SECURE_AREA_12345_project_name_country/data"
// global data_root "D:/Dropbox/ProjectName/data"
// global data_root "/mnt/network-drive/research/ProjectName/data"
// global data_root "C:/Users/YourName/Documents/Research/ProjectName/data"

/*------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    ADVANCED: Override individual data folders
------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

// If you only want to override specific folders, uncomment and edit:

// global data_raw "${data_root}/raw"
// global data_clean "${data_root}/clean"
// global data_final "${data_root}/final"

/*------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    NOTES
------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

// - Use forward slashes (/) in paths, even on Windows
// - Stata will convert them automatically
// - Paths can be absolute or relative
// - Use quotes if path contains spaces
